The BCM2837 SoC used in the Raspberry Pi 3 model B has the following cache
specifications:

The per-core L1 instruction cache is 16 KB, 2-way set associative, virtually
indexed and physically tagged, with 512 byte cache lines.

The per-core L1 data cache is 16 KB, 4-way set associative, physically indexed
and physically tagged, with 512 byte cache lines.

The shared L2 cache is 512 KB, 16-way set associative, physically indexed and
physically tagged, with 64 byte cache lines.
